<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="427" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,1050,1076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Diagnosis—</emphasis>
Integument papillae rounded. Genital plates with 40–51 pairs of Ac in at most four longitudinal rows. Numbers of leg swimming setae: II-L-posterior 1; III-L-4 posterior 6-7; III-L-5 posterior 5; IV-L-4 anterior 6-8, posterior 6-7; IV-L-5 anterior 2-3, posterior 4-5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="427" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1158,1184]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[359,485,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Both sexes</emphasis>
: Integument papillae rounded (
<figureCitation box="[867,962,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,187,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1897]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hydrodroma golestanica sp. nov. (A, C holotype ♂, B, ♀ paratype): A-B = genital field; C = integument papillae; D = photograph of dorsal integument in tangential view. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794936" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5794936/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Cx-I+II medially separated by a fine membranous line, with a row of long fine setae at medial margins of Cx-I, and posterior margins of Cx-I, Cx-II, -III, and –IV. Genital flaps with rounded lateral and concave medial margins (
<figureCitation box="[981,1055,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,187,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1897]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hydrodroma golestanica sp. nov. (A, C holotype ♂, B, ♀ paratype): A-B = genital field; C = integument papillae; D = photograph of dorsal integument in tangential view. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794936" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5794936/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
A-B). Excretory pore sclerotized. Leg claws with a dorsal clawlet.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis box="[199,257,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[271,374,1303,1329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">holotype</typeStatus>
; in parentheses some measurements of the 
<typeStatus box="[851,947,1303,1329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">paratype</typeStatus>
specimen [CCDB 38361 F03]): Idiosoma L 1130, W 1090. Coxal field L 527; Cx-III W 559, L Cx-I+II 266, Cx-III+IV 278; coxal setae numbers: Cx-I, 24 (23); Cx-II, 23 (22); Cx-III, 14 (18); Cx-IV 11 (19). Genital plate (
<figureCitation box="[835,922,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1921,1945]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,187,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[151,1436,181,1897]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Hydrodroma golestanica sp. nov. (A, C holotype ♂, B, ♀ paratype): A-B = genital field; C = integument papillae; D = photograph of dorsal integument in tangential view. Scale bars = 100 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794936" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5794936/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
) L 259 (238), on each plate Ac number 49-51 (49), with 36-40 setae, all hollow. Ejaculatory complex L 198.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">
Gnathosoma vL 228; chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[557,644,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1731,1755]" captionTargetBox="[201,1381,175,1702]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[189,1398,166,1715]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hydrodroma golestanica sp. nov., holotype ♂: A = palp, lateral view; B = palp, medial view (P-1 missing); C = gnathosoma; D = chelicera; E = IV-L-5 and -6, posterior view. Scale bars = 100 μm.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5794938/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) total L 297, L basal segment 238, claw 63, L ratio basal segment/claw 3.8. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[263,340,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1731,1755]" captionTargetBox="[201,1381,175,1702]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[189,1398,166,1715]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hydrodroma golestanica sp. nov., holotype ♂: A = palp, lateral view; B = palp, medial view (P-1 missing); C = gnathosoma; D = chelicera; E = IV-L-5 and -6, posterior view. Scale bars = 100 μm.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794938" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5794938/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
A-B) total L 444, dL/H, dL/H ratio: P-1, 55/45, 1.23; P-2, 73/56, 1.3; P-3, 50/53, 0.94; P-4, 186/47, 4.0; P-5, 80/22, 3.6; L ratio P-2/P-4, 0.4. dL IV-L: 128, 150, 200, 309, 313, 291.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis box="[199,283,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[299,400,1555,1581]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">paratype</typeStatus>
, n = 1; juvenile specimen ([CCDB 38361 F05]): Idiosoma L 790. Coxal field L 486; Cx-III W 494, L Cx-I+II 256, Cx-III+IV 281; coxal setae numbers: Cx-I, 18; Cx-II, 18; Cx-III, 13; Cx-IV 12. Genital plate large, L 210-217, on each plate Ac number 40-42, with 30 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Gnathosoma vL 228; chelicera total L 297, L basal segment 233, claw 63, L ratio basal segment/claw 3.7. Palp total L 446, dL/H, dL/H ratio: P-1, 53/45, 1.19; P-2, 77/57, 1.34; P-3, 52/55, 0.94; P-4, 189/42, 4.5; P-5, 75/22, 3.4; L ratio P-2/P-4, 0.41. dL IV-L: 125, 150, 205, 309, 328, 272.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,906,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,692,1770,1796]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Species delimitation using DNA-barcodes</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[691,716,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">—</emphasis>
The final alignment for species delimitation using COI sequence data of ten 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1837" box="[273,416,1807,1833]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[273,416,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Hydrodroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens listed in 
<tableCitation box="[637,718,1807,1833]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,239,777,801]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 2. List of Hydrodroma specimens used in this study." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF53662CFFB1FFB6FF2DFCBEED29FCDD" pageId="2" pageNumber="427" tableUuid="DF53662CFFB1FFB6FF2DFCBEED29FCDD">Table 2</tableCitation>
and one outgroup, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sokolow" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[930,1151,1807,1833]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Protzia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cabardinica">
<emphasis box="[930,1151,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Protzia cabardinica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(BOLD: 8. IR8 2017 H2) from 
<collectingCountry box="[212,257,1843,1869]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Iran</collectingCountry>
to root the tree. The NJ tree is presented in 
<figureCitation box="[742,808,1843,1869]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[188,1404,1213,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-346@6.[151,1436,1173,1836]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neighbor-joining tree based on studied Hydrodroma COI sequences. The optimal tree with the sum of branch length = 0.54910533 is shown. The analysis involved 11 nucleotide sequences. There were a total of 669 positions in the final dataset." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794940" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5794940/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
. The COI tree sequence retrieved from a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pešić &amp; Zawal &amp; Saboori &amp; Smit, 2021" authorityName="Pešić &amp; Zawal &amp; Saboori &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="golestanica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">H. golestanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[286,376,1879,1905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[286,369,1879,1905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[442,487,1879,1905]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Iran</collectingCountry>
appeared as a sister taxa of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walter" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[794,960,1879,1905]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torrenticola">
