<figureCitation box="[974,1041,1879,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[188,1404,1213,1819]" captionTargetId="figure-346@6.[151,1436,1173,1836]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Neighbor-joining tree based on studied Hydrodroma COI sequences. The optimal tree with the sum of branch length = 0.54910533 is shown. The analysis involved 11 nucleotide sequences. There were a total of 669 positions in the final dataset." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5794940" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5794940/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="427">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
